<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1526,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
Note:—This taxon was initially described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sledge, W. A." box="[720,881,1634,1660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref2998" refString="Sledge, W. A. (1981) The Thelypteridaceae of Ceylon. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Botany series 8: 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="1981">Sledge (1981)</bibRefCitation>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blume) Ching" authorityName="Ching" baseAuthorityName="Blume" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Metathelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[1071,1347,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Metathelypteris flaccida</emphasis>
(Blume) Ching
</taxonomicName>
considering its wide-creeping and branching rhizome. It was renamed 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1168,1670,1696]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Thelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dassanayakei">
<emphasis box="[990,1168,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">T. dassanayakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser-Jenkins, C. R." box="[1208,1451,1670,1696]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" refId="ref1979" refString="Fraser-Jenkins, C. R. (1997) New Species Syndrome in Indian Pteridology and the Ferns of Nepal. International Book Distributors, Dehra Dun, India, 403 pp." type="book" year="1997">Fraser-Jenkins (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and represents a different species from 
<emphasis box="[575,710,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<taxonomicName box="[575,706,1706,1732]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Metathelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">M. flaccida</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This endemic species occurs in high altitude areas (
<quantity box="[1290,1443,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.77" metricValueMax="2.09" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" unit="m" value="1770.0" valueMax="2090.0" valueMin="1450.0">1450-2090 m</quantity>
) and is considered as a critically endangered species (
<bibRefCitation author="Ranil, R. H. G. &amp; Gunawardena, N. P. T. &amp; Muthukudaarachchi, D. K. T. &amp; Pushpakumara, D. K. N. G. &amp; Wijesundara, D. S. A." box="[725,926,1742,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="170 - 188" refId="ref2800" refString="Ranil, R. H. G., Gunawardena, N. P. T., Muthukudaarachchi, D. K. T., Pushpakumara, D. K. N. G. &amp; Wijesundara, D. S. A. (2020) Pteridophytes in Sri Lanka. In: The National Red List 2020 (Org.) Conservation Status of the Flora of Sri Lanka. Sri Lanka, Biodiversity Secretariat of the Ministry of Environment and the National Herbarium, Department of the National Botanic Gardens, Peradeniya. pp. 170 - 188." type="book chapter" year="2020">
Ranil 
<emphasis box="[795,851,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
